.TH "us5182d_update_dark_th" 9 "us5182d_update_dark_th" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
us5182d_update_dark_th \- update Darh_Th registers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" us5182d_update_dark_th
.BI "(struct us5182d_data *data "  ","
.BI "int index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
us5182d_data structure
.IP "index" 12
index in us5182d_dark_ths array to use for the updated value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Function needs to be called with a lock held because it needs two i2c write
byte operations as these registers (0x27 0x28) don't work in word mode
accessing.
